delegated performance arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe featured archive gallery delegated performance the delegated performance mini conference looked at the practice of delegated performance in different arts from different perspectives and through different forms since the early days of performance art in the 1970s and the heyday of solo performance in the 1980s the concept of performer's agency has changed significantly while some artists still perform their works themselves many others are now hiring nonprofessional performers to execute their ideas similarly parallel to those artists who are subverting the rules of art institutions others are collaborating with curators and theater managers in order to turn them into the very means of artistic expression both the means and the outcomes of this kind of performance are more often than not controversial and they raise a number of ethical political and theoretical questions the participants in this conference looked at the practice of delegated performance in different arts visual art theater from different perspectives art history performance studies museum curatorship activism and through different forms presentation dialogue round table workshop stanford humanities center website michael silverman sica photographer 2010 2011 home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
